parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failure can cause various components to malfunction, leading to safety risks, such as loss of control, accidents, or even fires.
symptoms: heater fan blower motor works intermittently
wiring harness to heater under the glovebox is burning hot
plastic wire harness component is completely destroyed
and other gauges work only sometimes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Instrument cluster failure can cause the driver to lose critical information, such as speed, RPM, and other vital gauges, leading to safety risks, accidents, or tickets.
symptoms: speedometer and other gauges work only sometimes
and instrument cluster resets itself periodically.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Windshield wiper system failure can cause reduced visibility, leading to accidents or safety risks, especially during rain or snow.
symptoms: windshield washer motor runs without control
windshield washer pump turns on without warning
and windshield washer fluid tank motor burns
and is on the verge of causing serious damage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the windshield wipers can cause reduced visibility while driving, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially in inclement weather conditions.
symptoms: wipers and washer pump operate when the vehicle is turned off
and wipers and washer pump cannot be controlled by the driver.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical issues can cause various systems to malfunction, leading to safety risks and inconvenience to the driver.
symptoms: Radio stays on when the vehicle is turned off

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the SDM can cause the airbag warning light to remain illuminated, indicating a potential safety risk, and may prevent the airbags from deploying in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The airbag warning light remains illuminated
the airbag system fails to function
and other electrical accessories may malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water ingress into the vehicle can cause the SDM to malfunction, leading to airbag system failure, which can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of a crash.
symptoms: particularly through the roof drainage system
and accumulates on the front floorboard

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The discontinuation of the SDM part for the 2005 Hummer H2 model year can leave owners without a replacement option, potentially compromising the safety of the vehicle.
symptoms: Owners are unable to find a replacement SDM part
and dealerships and independent shops are unable to assist due to the discontinued part.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake booster can cause the brake pedal to become stiff or go to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels stiff or goes to the floor
brake pedal is difficult to press
brake pedal makes a whistling sound
steering wheel becomes difficult to turn.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake lines can cause the brake pedal to go to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Brake pedal goes to the floor

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
